# Cursor rule authoring

- **Never set `alwaysApply: true`.** Use `alwaysApply: false` and scope with `globs` so rules attach when relevant files are in context.
- One concern per rule file; keep under ~50 lines; prefer actionable bullets over prose.
- Use `description` for the rule picker; frontmatter must be valid YAML.

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
---
description: Source conventions
globs: src/**/*.py
alwaysApply: false
---

# ❌ BAD
---
description: Everything
alwaysApply: true
---
```
